<subSubSection id="0FC96579FFE9896D7DCDA2B2B9F0FD44" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFE9896D7DCDA2B2BB84FD7B" blockId="63.[151,1436,151,371]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE9896D7DCDA2B2BB63FC86" bold="true" box="[199,320,151,177]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE9896D7C43A2BDBBF2FC86" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1839" box="[329,465,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE9896D7C43A2BDBBF2FC86" box="[329,465,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the New World, with a few species being described from South America (
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE9896D7C57A29BBBF5FCEF" box="[349,470,190,216]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Argentina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="63" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Argentina</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectingCountry id="3FC47662FFE9896D7CECA29BB813FCEF" box="[486,560,190,216]" name="Brazil" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="3FC47662FFE9896D7F7FA29BB8F6FCEF" box="[629,725,190,216]" name="Guyana" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Guyana</collectingCountry>
), and the 
<typeStatus id="98688850FFE9896D7E45A29BB9A2FCEF" box="[847,897,190,216]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
species being recorded from as far north as British Columbia and Massachusetts, across the Caribbean, and south to Tierra del Fuego. A record for 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE9896D7D9DA329B861FD11" authority="(Fieber 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Fieber" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[151,578,268,294]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveolata">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE9896D7D9DA329BBB6FD12" box="[151,405,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Xerophloea foveolata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFE9896D7CADA329B819FD11" author="Fieber, F. X." box="[423,570,268,294]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="497 - 516" refId="ref56686" refString="Fieber, F. X. (1866) Neue Gattungen und Arten in Homoptern (Cicadina Bur.). Verhandlungen de Kaiserlich - Koniglichen Zoologisch - botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 16, 497 - 516." type="journal article" year="1866">Fieber 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from Southern Europe (Metcalf 1962) is probably an error, as 
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFE9896D7835A329BAC7FD7B" author="Szwedo, J." pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="153 - 163" refId="ref59765" refString="Szwedo, J. (2002) Studies on Xerophloeini leafhoppers with description of Pariacaca icanoensis gen. and sp. nov. from Argentina (Hemiptera: Cicadomorpha: Cicadellidae: Ledrinae). Genus, 13, 153 - 163." type="journal article" year="2002">Szwedo (2002)</bibRefCitation>
has pointed out.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFE9896D7DCDA37CB9F0FD44" blockId="63.[151,1436,151,371]" box="[199,979,345,371]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
The last revision of 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE9896D7CBBA37CB81AFD45" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1839" box="[433,569,345,370]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE9896D7CBBA37CB81AFD45" box="[433,569,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was performed by 
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFE9896D7E11A37CB9ECFD44" author="Nielson, M. W." box="[795,975,345,371]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="234 - 244" refId="ref58885" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1962) A revision of the genus Xerophloea (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 55, 234 - 244." type="journal article" year="1962">Nielson (1962)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
